TITLE: Installing Ignite UI for jQuery CLI
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to install and use the Ignite UI for jQuery CLI to create a new project, add a component, and start the development server. It relies on npm for package management and assumes the user has Node.js installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
npm i -g igniteui-cli
ig new <project name> --framework=jquery
cd <project name>
ig add combo <component name>
ig start
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Ignite UI via npm
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the command to install the Ignite UI package using npm. This assumes npm is installed and configured correctly and will install the latest version of the ignite-ui package.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
npm install ignite-ui
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Including Ignite UI Files
DESCRIPTION: These script tags demonstrate how to include the necessary Ignite UI JavaScript files in your HTML.  The paths assume the files are located in either the node_modules or bower_components directory after installation.  These lite versions provide optimized functionalities.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<script src="<node_modules|bower_components>/ignite-ui/js/infragistics.core-lite.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
<script src="<node_modules|bower_components>/ignite-ui/js/infragistics.lob-lite.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Importing LESS files in correct order
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the correct order for importing LESS files in an Infragistics theme to ensure proper functionality. It includes variable definitions, mixins, font styles, jQuery UI theme styles, and module styles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/src/css/themes/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
// Ignite UI for jQuery Theme variables
@import "variables.less";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Mixins
@import "mixins.less";

// Font styles
@import (css)"icons-styles.css";

// JQuery UI Theme
@import "framework.less";

//Ignite UI for jQuery modules
@import "modules/modules";
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: LESS File Import Order
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the crucial order in which LESS files must be imported within the `infragistics.theme.less` file. The correct order ensures proper variable and style definitions for Ignite UI for jQuery components to function correctly. It starts with Bootstrap and Ignite UI variables, followed by mixins, icon styles, jQuery UI styles, and finally, Ignite UI component styles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/src/css/themes/bootstrap4/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: LESS
CODE:
```
// Bootstrap Theme variables
@import "variables";

// Ignite UI for jQuery variables
@import "ignite-ui-variables";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Mixins
@import "mixins";

// Icons fonts
@import "icons-styles.css";

//JQuery UI
@import "framework";

//Ignite UI for jQuery styles
@import "modules/modules";
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: File Import Order in infragistics.theme.less
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the required order of file imports within the `infragistics.theme.less` file.  The order is crucial for the correct application of styles and variables.  The file includes bootstrap variables, ignite ui variables and mixins, jquery ui styles, ignite ui styles and font styles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/src/css/themes/bootstrap3/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
// Bootstrap Theme variables
@import "variables.less";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Theme variables
@import "ignite-ui-variables";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Mixins
@import "mixins.less";

//JQuery UI
@import "framework.less";

//Ignite UI for jQuery styles
@import "modules/modules.less";

// Font styles
@import (css)"icons-styles.css";
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Import Order in infragistics.theme.less
DESCRIPTION: Defines the correct order for importing files within the `infragistics.theme.less` file. Maintaining this order is crucial for the theme to function correctly, ensuring proper variable and style dependencies are resolved.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/src/css/themes/bootstrap4/README.ja.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
// Bootstrap Theme variables
@import "variables";

// Ignite UI for jQuery variables
@import "ignite-ui-variables";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Mixins
@import "mixins";

// Icons fonts
@import "icons-styles.css";

//JQuery UI
@import "framework";

//Ignite UI for jQuery styles
@import "modules/modules";
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: LESS Import Order
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the order in which LESS files should be imported within the `infragistics.theme.less` file. Maintaining this order is crucial for the correct functioning of the theme. The order includes Bootstrap variables, Ignite UI variables, mixins, jQuery UI framework styles, Ignite UI module styles, and icon styles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/src/css/themes/bootstrap3/README.ja.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: LESS
CODE:
```
// Bootstrap Theme variables
@import "variables.less";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Theme variables
@import "ignite-ui-variables";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Mixins
@import "mixins.less";

//JQuery UI
@import "framework.less";

//Ignite UI for jQuery styles
@import "modules/modules.less";

// Font styles
@import (css)"icons-styles.css";
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: LESS File Import Order
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the order in which LESS files should be imported for Infragistics jQuery themes. It ensures proper compilation and functionality by importing variables, mixins, font styles, the jQuery UI framework, and Ignite UI for jQuery modules in a specific sequence. This order is crucial for the theme to work correctly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/src/css/themes/README.ja.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
// Ignite UI for jQuery Theme variables
@import "variables.less";

// Ignite UI for jQuery Mixins
@import "mixins.less";

// Font styles
@import (css)"icons-styles.css";

// JQuery UI Theme
@import "framework.less";

//Ignite UI for jQuery modules
@import "modules/modules";
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Ignite UI with Bower
DESCRIPTION: This command installs the Ignite UI package using Bower, a package manager for the web. This will download the necessary files into your project's bower_components directory, allowing you to use Ignite UI components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
bower install ignite-ui
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Install Ignite UI for jQuery with Bower
DESCRIPTION: This command installs the Ignite UI for jQuery library using Bower. Bower is a package manager for the web.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/build/packages/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
bower install ignite-ui
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Dependencies using npm
DESCRIPTION: This command installs all necessary dependencies for the project, including build dependencies and Bower packages used in the demos. It must be run in the root directory of the repository after cloning it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
npm install
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Building Ignite UI Project
DESCRIPTION: This command builds the Ignite UI project using Grunt, a JavaScript task runner. It creates source files under the `dist/` folder, including merged locales, combined scripts, and structure CSS. This command can be run again after making changes to include them in the build.
SOURCE: https://github.com/igniteui/ignite-ui/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
grunt build
```
